HEADWORD: Rhododendron
<hw>Rho`do*den"dron</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<grk>"rodo`dendron</grk>, literally, rose tree; <grk>"ro`don</grk> rose
+ <grk>de`ndron</grk> tree. See <er>Rose</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A genus of shrubs or small trees, often having handsome evergreen
leaves, and remarkable for the beauty of their flowers;
rosebay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

